basics.name: Min Thet Naing
basics.label: Programmer
basics.summary: My previous experiences and projects were mainly specialised in web development: backend, front-end, and to server deployment.   Although ruby is my strongest language, I also have great deal of interests in different programming paradigms. The concepts are those which please me not the syntax.  I always keep abreast with the web technology trends. I like to read and learn new things on daily basic for both professional and personal growth

highlights: Built Internal Dashboard for tracking sales and customers across different marketplace
Implemented automation for some of the daily checking and updating tasks
Wrote a chrome extension to interact with our amazon storefronts
Wrote RESTful API for different clients' projects (ruby on rails)
Helped write Media Asset Management in C# on ASP.Net
Built with React, Redux, Redux-Thunk, Python, GeoJson, Google Maps, Mapbox, SASS, ImmutableJS

awards.title: Fujitsu Prize Australia
awards.summary: Our Team of 4 people were awarded Fujitsu Prize for our last year final project. We delivered 'A-code generator' which basically generate 3-Tier Architecture in ASP.Net based on user configuration and set of rules.

references.name: Ye Mon Kyaw
references.reference: He is young, talented and passionate developer, quick learner, always improving himself and keeping in touch with latest technology.
